The 36 governors are meeting today to review a number of critical issues surrounding the financial autonomy for the state judiciary and legislature, code-named the Executive Order 10, 2020. Head, Media and Public Affairs of the Nigerian Governors Forum (NGF), Abdulrazaque Bello-Barkindo, who disclosed this in a statement yesterday in Abuja, said the meeting, like eight others before it, would have in attendance all the chief executives via Microsoft Team from their various states. He added that the governors would equally deliberate on NLNG ownership, the controversial NCDC Bill, the restructuring of statesâ€™ loans and Federation Accounts Allocation Committee (FAAC) deductions. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .